******
[2] Philippines
Date: Sat 21 Jul 2012
Source: philSTAR.com, Xinhua report [edited]
http://www.philstar.com/Article.aspx?articleId=829985&publicationSubCategoryId=200


Gov't seeks public's help against EV-71
---------------------------------------
The Department of Health (DOH) earlier reported that a 19-month-old toddler from Davao City in southern Philippines has been infected with human enterovirus 71 (EV-71), the same virus that has killed more than 60 children in Cambodia. The boy was the only confirmed case among 8 suspected cases in the country with the hand, foot and mouth disease, Health Secretary Enrique Ona has said. The [virus] strain detected in the boy was a mild form of EV-71 and could have been in the country long before its deadlier variant killed Cambodian children, Ona noted.

In an interview with state-run radio station, Presidential Spokesman Edwin Lacierda [gave assurances] that the Department of Health (DOH) is preparing to handle EV-71. "We need the participation of the citizenry. If you feel that there are symptoms that would lead to EV-71 infection, immediately bring [them] to the attention of the doctors," he said. He said a person should not wait for the illness to become serious before going to a hospital.

